Healthy growth in corporate profits and in consumer spending, the two pillars on which Japan rests its hopes of sustained economic growth, both look rotten at the core, economists polled by Reuters said
Profits and domestic consumption are meant to replace exports as the engine of growth
But close ties between corporate performance and wages mean that the alternative economic model promises little but slower growth, they said
Falling profits may lead to falling incomes, which in turn will cut sales and further reduce profits
The Bank of Japan said in its latest outlook that improved terms of trade linked to the strong yen would help domestic demand grow steadily
