The latest measures follow recent moves to abolish the maximum interest rates banks can offer for some peseta funds and the lifting of restrictions on investments abroad by Spaniards
The government has also allowed foreign companies to be quoted on Spanish stock exchanges and has promised further reforms of the domestic financial system
